  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-03-02",
    "date": "2021-04-23T10:57:39Z",
    "text": "Veterans Access to Direct Primary Care Act\n\nThis bill requires the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) to implement a five-year pilot program to provide eligible veterans with the option to receive primary care services from a non-VA health care provider under a direct primary care service arrangement through the use of a veteran health savings account. Eligible veterans are those enrolled in the VA health care system."
  },
